<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-08T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="661" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 PW/8–445:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-08T20:00:00-04:00">August 8, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>1225. Your 1284, Aug. 4. We would regard raising of question at
                                    this juncture in Sub-Commission as unfortunate and we desire
                                    that you exert every effort as discreetly as possible to prevent
                                    it. If nevertheless question is raised in Sub-Commission inform
                                    Dept. and instructions in matter will be sent.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>